oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Aerial of Cayce Hojmes Project Site, 1940
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Photograph showing the James A. Cayce Homes project site (Projects Tenn. 5-1 and Tenn. 5-1A), 11 February 1940. The Cayce Homes were built between 1939 and 1941 as a white-only community, designed by Marr & Holman. Forms part of the MDHA Photograph Collection. 1 photograph : b & w.
